<p><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt'>Artillery Analysis at the Battle of Fredericksburg</span></b></p>

<p></p>

<p><b>Introduction</b></p>

<p>The Battle of Fredericksburg was fought between General
Robert E. Lee&acute;s Confederate Army of Northern Virginia and the Major General
Ambrose E. Burnside&acute;s Union Army of the Potomac. It is remembered as one of the
most one-sided battles of the American Civil War in which the Union Army
suffered terrible casualties in frontal assaults on entrenched Confederate
defenders. It is also remembered as one of the most significant artillery
engagements of the war, which is the driving force behind the analysis.</p>

<p></p>

<p><img width=458
height=285 src="image001.jpg" ></p>

<p></p>

<p><b>Target Audience</b></p>

<p>The audience for this project could really be anyone from
someone just curious about the battle to a student doing a research project on
the effectiveness of artillery in battle. The visuals in the project give
someone that is just taking a glance a good impression of how effective
artillery was used. On the other hand, if someone is doing research on the
battle, they can click on the individual batteries to get a picture and more
detail.</p>

<p></p>

<p><b></b></p>

<p><b></b></p>

